<title type="html"><![CDATA[Canvas Proposal: point of origin parameter for rotate()]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="https://forums.whatwg.org/bb3/viewtopic.php?t=48&amp;p=215#p215"><![CDATA[
You can do this with a function like<br /><dl class="codebox"><dt>Code: </dt><dd><code>function rotateAround&#40;ctx, a, x, y&#41;<br />&#123;<br />    ctx.translate&#40;x, y&#41;;<br />    ctx.rotate&#40;a&#41;;<br />    ctx.translate&#40;-x, -y&#41;;<br />&#125;</code></dd></dl>and then call e.g. <dl class="codebox"><dt>Code: </dt><dd><code>rotateAround&#40;ctx, 0.5, 50, 50&#41;</code></dd></dl>which should produce the desired effect. (I think it'd be useful to have a library for this kind of stuff, if people find it useful but if it's not worth making part of the spec.)<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="https://forums.whatwg.org/bb3/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=91">Philip</a> — Thu May 10, 2007 1:19 am</p><hr />
